## Theme kindly inspired from
## http://nongeekshandbook.blogspot.ie/2009/03/mutt-color-configuration.html
## Adapted by alex.kraker@gmail.com for native terminal background/foreground
## and other adjustments

## Colours for items in the index
color index color13 default ~N # New
color index color13 default ~O # Old - brightred looks bad
color index color12 default ~R # Read
color index color4 default ~D # Deleted Mails - use dark color as they are already "dealt with"
color index color2 default ~Q # Replied
color index color1 default ~F # Flagged -
color index color3 color2 ~T # Tagged -

mono index bold ~N
mono index bold ~F
mono index bold ~T

## Highlights inside the body of a message.

## URLs
color body color12 default "(http|https|ftp|news|telnet|finger)://[^ \"\t\r\n]*"
color body color12 default "mailto:[-a-z_0-9.]+@[-a-z_0-9.]+"
mono body bold "(http|https|ftp|news|telnet|finger)://[^ \"\t\r\n]*"
mono body bold "mailto:[-a-z_0-9.]+@[-a-z_0-9.]+"

## Email addresses.
color body color2 default "[-a-z_0-9.%$]+@[-a-z_0-9.]+\\.[-a-z][-a-z]+"

